        private static java.nio.file.Path getFilePath​(java.lang.Class<?> token,
                                              java.nio.file.Path root,
                                              boolean end)
        Returns the Path to the implementation of token relative from the root. Implementation of token has suffix Impl. Also the path has suffix dependent on end.
        Parameters:
        token - type token to create the implementation's path to
        root - root directory
        end - if true then add .java to the suffix of path if false then add .class to the suffix of path
        Returns:
        path to the implementation of token starting from root

      • implement

        public void implement​(java.lang.Class<?> token,
                      java.nio.file.Path root)
               throws ImplerException
        Produces code implementing class or interface specified by provided token.

        Generated class full name is same as full name of the type token with Impl suffix added. Generated source code is placed in the correct subdirectory of the specified root directory and have correct file name. For example, the implementation of the interface List goes to $root/java/util/ListImpl.java

        Specified by:
        implement in interface Impler
        Parameters:
        token - type token to create implementation for.
        root - root directory.
        Throws:
        ImplerException - when implementation cannot be generated

      • writeClassName

        private void writeClassName​(java.lang.Class<?> token,
                            java.io.Writer writer)
                     throws java.io.IOException
        Writes information about token's implementation name by writer. Implementation class have same modifiers as token except abstract and interface (implementation does not have these modifiers). Also it writes the '{' and two '\n' symbols in the end.
        Parameters:
        token - type token to create implementation for
        writer - a writer
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - if an I/O error occurs

      • writeConstructors

        private void writeConstructors​(java.lang.Class<?> token,
                               java.io.Writer writer)
                        throws java.io.IOException,
                               ImplerException
        Writes implementation of constructors of token's implementation by writer. Private constructors are ignored. Also token have to have at least one non-private declared constructor or it has to be an interface. Otherwise, this method throws an ImplerException.
        Parameters:
        token - type token to create implementation for
        writer - a writer
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - if an I/O error occurs
        ImplerException - if token is not an interface and it has only private declared constructors

      • writeExecutable

        private void writeExecutable​(java.lang.reflect.Executable executable,
                             java.io.Writer writer,
                             java.lang.Class<?> token)
                      throws java.io.IOException
        Writes signature of implementation of executable by writer. Signature includes also what executable throws. This method does not write '{' in the end however it writes space after list of exceptions. Modifiers in the result signature are same with executable's modifiers except abstract and transient (implementation does not have these modifiers). *
        Parameters:
        executable - Executable of token which this method declares
        writer - a writer
        token - type token to create implementation for
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - if an I/O error occurs

      • writeConstructorImpl

        private void writeConstructorImpl​(java.lang.reflect.Constructor<?> constructor,
                                  java.io.Writer writer)
                           throws java.io.IOException
        Writes body of constructor by writer. The body starts with '{' and ends with '}'. The implementation of constructor is calling super() with arguments of the constructor.
        Parameters:
        constructor - Constructor which this method defines
        writer - a writer
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - if an I/O error occurs

      • getDefaultReturnType

        private java.lang.String getDefaultReturnType​(java.lang.Class<?> type)
        Returns string with default value of type. If type is void it returns empty string. Otherwise, if it is boolean then it returns " true". Otherwise, if it is primitive method returns " 0". Otherwise, it returns " null".
        Parameters:
        type - type which of default value method returns
        Returns:
        string with default value of type with space in beginning (if type is not void)
